[SN]TITLE[SN]
Academic Jeroen Ensink death: Indefinite hospital order for killer

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A student who killed an academic who had gone out to post cards announcing the birth of his daughter is given an indefinite hospital order.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Nigerian Femi Nandap, 23, stabbed Jeroen Ensink, 41, to death in Islington, north London, while in a psychotic rage last December.
He carried out the attack on Dr Ensink days after knife and assault charges against him were dropped
Nandap had admitted manslaughter by diminished responsibility.
